Final numeric calculation
- Technology Adoption: 19/25  
- Innovation Leadership: 17/25  
- Measurable Impact: 18/25  
- Future Strategy: 13/15  
- Industry Position: 8/10

Total = 19 + 17 + 18 + 13 + 8 = 75/100

Overall assessment
Wabtec is a credible, well‑resourced participant in rail decarbonization with tangible sustainable technologies deployed (notably FLXdrive battery platforms, Trip Optimizer and remanufacturing) and strong partnerships (national labs, major freight customers). The company has produced measurable operational emissions reductions and a clear roadmap (50% Scope 1/2 by 2030, Scope 3 disclosure and supplier engagement). It scores as a top performer in freight/industrial rail sustainable technology adoption, though it is not the single dominant leader across all rail segments when compared with large passenger-focused OEMs (Alstom, Siemens) that show larger public R&D budgets and earlier large-scale hydrogen/battery passenger deployments.

